catch up -------- if you haven't seen the kickoff or feel behind, you
can [click here](https://buildspace.so/s4/start) to go to all the
kickoff steps --- pretty simple + easy to catch up. the steps are also
available in the os. we highly recommend you to install the extension or
bookmark the [os page](https://buildspace.so/home). weekly update is due
monday, august 14 @ 11:59pm pt extended till thursday, august 17 @
11:59pm
pt. ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
you must watch the first lecture to fully understand what all is needed
for the first week. again the [link to the
recording](https://buildspace.so/home) is in the os. the weekly update
is a simple form you fill out each week, check it out real quick and
scroll through it to get an idea of what you gotta submit. [click here
to submit update 1](https://buildspace.so/s4/update/1) a few things are
required for weekly update #1: 1 --- get the template & make your idea
slide. -------------------------------------------- first, you'll need
to create you idea slide on figma via the template we used in the
lecture. you can find the template
[here](https://www.figma.com/community/file/1270587903079571101) or on
the os. all the instructions are part of the template.
![](https://framerusercontent.com/images/suQnoBijfmdb5exfkBEi4TlFI.jpg)
2 --- post it on ig / x / linkedin / wherever so we + others in s4 can
see :)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
you can tag @_buildspace or @_nightsweekends for twitter, or @buildspace
on linkedin if you want your post to get more visibility. i recommend
you "cc" us like this.
![](https://framerusercontent.com/images/XTebeuMTVc2ekQXFmq8u7qftLec.png)
3 --- give feedback to five others. ---------------------------------
you'll need to publicly give 5 other individuals feedback on their idea
on twitter or linkedin, simply reply to their idea slide and give them
your honest take about their idea. [view latest ideas on
twitter](https://twitter.com/search?q=(%40_buildspace%20OR%20%40_nightsweekends)%20-filter%3Areplies%20filter%3Aimages&src=typed_query&f=live)
[view trending ideas on
twitter](https://twitter.com/search?q=(%40_buildspace%20OR%20%40_nightsweekends)%20-filter%3Areplies%20filter%3Aimages&src=typed_query)
[view latest ideas on
linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/search/results/content/?datePosted=%22past-week%22&keywords=%40buildspace&origin=FACETED_SEARCH&sid=Q%2CR&sortBy=%22date_posted%22)
[view trending ideas on
linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/search/results/content/?datePosted=%22past-24h%22&keywords=%40buildspace&origin=FACETED_SEARCH&sid=nTL&sortBy=%22relevance%22)
[scroll through reels/posts on ig (click on
tagged)](https://www.instagram.com/_buildspace)
![](https://framerusercontent.com/images/xIrmGefA1n91YTpKJAPfdofGPc.png)
this is your time to explore people in s4, and also follow the ones you
think are working on something cool. this is what i meant by "meeting
people in the wild". optional: we also got ig reels
------------------------------ we've created a [really simple
tutorial]() for you all to post your idea slide to reels. the template
is the figma slide you opened in figma earlier. you need to understand,
you + your idea slide can go viral. you are a person working on your own
idea, there aren't many like you. plus -- it's simple af, and you should
take a shot. [here is jeffrey's example for
reference.](https://www.instagram.com/reel/CvrG88VPegy/?utm_source=ig_web_copy_link)
that's all! if you have questions, ping <support@buildspace.so> -- we
reply to every email.
